<div id="about-the-community" class="section-spacer">
    <h2 class="sect-title">About Greenwood/Greenbriar </h2>
    <div class="col-grid-2">
        <div>
        <p class="par-lg">Perched atop a gentle hill slope at an elevation of 1,120 m from sea level, the community in Greenwood/Greenbriar houses a population of approximately 1000 people that reside in a total of 501 residential dwellings.</p>

        <p class="par-lg">Greenwood/Greenbriar real estate majorly comprises of a mobile home park and a Greenwood village that largely consists of single family detached homes and mobile residential units. Nearly 10.9% of all housing units in Greenwood/Greenbriar have been listed for renting, with most of the for-sale detached homes available at a competitive price of nearly $100,000.</p>

        <p class="par-xl">Due to the almost untouched nature of the neighborhood, Greenwood/Greenbriar homes for sale are quite popular. Residents enjoy the scenic atmosphere and the serenity that comes with it.</p>

        <p class="par-lg">With close proximity to local parks such as the Bowness Park, the Bowmont Park, the Athletic Park, the Shouldice Pool and the Edworthy park, the Greenwood/Greenbriar neighborhood offers plenty natural escapes for its residents to unwind after a hectic day at work. At the south of the neighborhood, you will also find the Canada Olympic Park.</p>


